'''Kōyashiki Kofun''' (甲屋敷古墳, ''Kōyashiki Kofun'') is a [[kofun]] (ancient Kofun) from the [[Kofun period]], located in [[Komaki]], [[:en:Aichi Prefecture|Aichi Prefecture]], Japan. It is part of the [[Koki Kofun Cluster]].
== Overview == The mound is estimated to have been constructed in the late [[:en:3rd century|3rd century]] to the [[:en:4th century|4th century]]. Approximately two-thirds of the mound has been lost<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Kōyashiki Kofun|url=http://www.city.komaki.aichi.jp/admin/soshiki/kyoiku/bunkazai/1_1/2/bunkazai/shiteibunkazai/4/9126.html|website=Komaki City Official Website|accessdate=2021-09-03|language=ja}}</ref>. During soil extraction work in the early [[Shōwa period]], a large quantity of red [[pigment]] and a [[Triangular-Rimmed Divine Beast Mirror|Triangular-rimmed Shinjukyo mirror]] were unearthed<ref name=":0" />. A portion of the burial chamber was discovered during a Komaki City historical survey in [[:en:1975|1975]]<ref name=":0" />. On [[March 25]], [[:en:1978|1978]], the triangular-rimmed Shinjukyo mirror was Historic Site1 as a tangible [[cultural property]] by Komaki City<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Triangular-rimmed Shinjukyo mirror unearthed from Kōyashiki Kofun (on display at Komaki City History Museum)|url=http://www.city.komaki.aichi.jp/admin/soshiki/kyoiku/bunkazai/1_1/2/bunkazai/shiteibunkazai/4/9127.html|website=Komaki City Official Website|accessdate=2021-09-03|language=ja}}</ref>. On [[:en:August 15|August 15]], [[:en:1992|1992]] ([[Heisei]] 4), the Kofun was Historic Site1 as a historic site by Komaki City<ref name=":0" />.
== burial goods == * Triangular-rimmed Shinjukyo mirror: Measuring 20.8 cm in diameter, it is believed to have been manufactured in Japan during the [[Kofun period]]<ref name=":1" />. The artifact is currently preserved and displayed at the [[Komaki City History Museum]]<ref name=":1" />. * Red pigment
== location == 2-474-1 Koki, [[Komaki City]], [[:en:Aichi Prefecture|Aichi Prefecture]]
== Access == * A 3-minute walk from the Koki [[bus stop]] served by [[Meitetsu Bus]].
== notes == {{notes}} <references />
== See Also == * [[Koki Kofun Cluster]] – A general term for the Kofuns in this area.
== External Links == * [http://www.city.komaki.aichi.jp/admin/soshiki/kyoiku/bunkazai/1_1/2/bunkazai/shiteibunkazai/4/9126.html Kōyashiki Kofun] * [http://www.city.komaki.aichi.jp/admin/soshiki/kyoiku/bunkazai/1_1/2/bunkazai/shiteibunkazai/4/9127.html Triangular-rimmed Shinjukyo mirror unearthed from Kōyashiki Kofun] * [http://www.city.komaki.aichi.jp/admin/event_1/events/bunkazai/2/1/13694.html Koki Kofuns]
